half automating the function for two arguments

def rest_locations(url, restaurant_name):
    response = requests.get(url)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, "html.parser")
    locations = soup.find_all("li", attrs={"class": ""})

    rows = []

    for location in locations:
        a_text = location.get_text()
        before = re.findall(r".+(?= " + re.escape(restaurant_name) + " locations )", a_text)
        after = re.findall(r"(?<=locations ).+", a_text)

        if before and after:
            state = before[0]
            numloc = after[0]
            numloc = numloc.replace("(","").replace(")","")

            rows.append({
                "state": state,
                "Number_of_Locations": numloc
            })

    return pd.DataFrame(rows)

Putting it all together

def rest_locations(url):
    response = requests.get(url)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, "html.parser")
    locations = soup.find_all("li", attrs={"class": ""})

    rest_name = soup.find("meta", attrs={"property":"og:title", "name":'og:title'})
    restaurant_name = rest_name.get("content")

    rows = []

    for location in locations:
        a_text = location.get_text()
        before = re.findall(r".+(?= " + re.escape(restaurant_name) + " locations )", a_text)
        after = re.findall(r"(?<=locations ).+", a_text)

        if before and after:
            state = before[0]
            numloc = after[0]
            numloc = numloc.replace("(","").replace(")","")

            rows.append({
                "state": state,
                "Number_of_Locations": numloc
            })

    return pd.DataFrame(rows)

def stateabb(state):
  states_dic = {
        "Alabama": "AL", "Alaska": "AK", "Arizona": "AZ", "Arkansas": "AR", "California": "CA",

        "Hawaii": "HI", "Idaho": "ID", "Illinois": "IL", "Indiana": "IN", "Iowa": "IA",
        "Kansas": "KS", "Kentucky": "KY", "Louisiana": "LA", "Maine": "ME", "Maryland": "MD",
        "Massachusetts": "MA", "Michigan": "MI", "Minnesota": "MN", "Mississippi": "MS", "Missouri": "MO",
        "Montana": "MT", "Nebraska": "NE", "Nevada": "NV", "New Hampshire": "NH", "New Jersey": "NJ",

def stock_data(stock_ticker):
    URL = "https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/" + stock_ticker + "/"
    response = requests.get(URL)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, "html.parser")
    stk_price = soup.find_all("div", attrs={"id": "Lead-5-QuoteHeader-Proxy"})

    rows = []

    for price in stk_price:
        price_tag = price.find('fin-streamer', attrs={'class': "Fw(b) Fz(36px) Mb(-4px) D(ib)"})
        prices = price_tag.get_text(strip=True)

        company_tag = price.find("h1", attrs={'class': "D(ib) Fz(18px)"})
        company = company_tag.get_text(strip=True)

        rows.append({
            "Company": company,
            "Stock Price": prices
        })

    stkprices = pd.DataFrame(rows)
    return stkprices

# Function to get data for multiple stock tickers
def multiple_stock_data(stock_tickers):
    result_dfs = []

    for ticker in stock_tickers:
        result_df = stock_data(ticker)
        result_dfs.append(result_df)

    combined_df = pd.concat(result_dfs, ignore_index=True)
    return combined_df
tickers = ["SBUX", "MCD", "AAPL"]
result_df = multiple_stock_data(tickers)

From Question 1 since i had it done there

def rest_locations(url):
    response = requests.get(url)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, "html.parser")
    locations = soup.find_all("li", attrs={"class": ""})

    rest_name = soup.find("meta", attrs={"property":"og:title", "name":'og:title'})
    restaurant_name = rest_name.get("content")

    rows = []

    for location in locations:
        a_text = location.get_text()
        before = re.findall(r".+(?= " + re.escape(restaurant_name) + " locations )", a_text)
        after = re.findall(r"(?<=locations ).+", a_text)

        if before and after:
            state = before[0]
            numloc = after[0]
            numloc = numloc.replace("(","").replace(")","")

            rows.append({
                "state": state,
                "Number_of_Locations": numloc,
                "Restaurant_Name": restaurant_name
            })

    return pd.DataFrame(rows)
